---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import WaitlistV2 from '../../components/v2/WaitlistV2.astro';
import WaitlistFormV2 from '../../components/v2/WaitlistFormV2.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Couples Food System V2" description="Our story — why we built Couples Food System and our mission to remove the mental load of meal planning." version="v2">
  <section class="py-20 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-6 text-v2-on-surface">Our Story</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Brand Story Image -->
    <div class="rounded-3xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg border border-v2-outline-variant mb-12">
      <img src="/images/v2/about-story.webp" alt="A couple's hands preparing fresh vegetables together on a wooden table in a sun-drenched kitchen with sage green and terracotta accents" class="w-full h-auto" decoding="async" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-v2-surface-container-lowest p-8 md:p-16 rounded-3xl border border-v2-outline-variant shadow-sm space-y-6 text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        It started in our own kitchen. I wanted to lean out, and my partner wanted to build muscle. Suddenly, Sunday meal prep became a nightmare of two different recipes, two grocery lists, and twice the cleanup.
      </p>
      <p>
        We tried standard meal planning apps, but they felt clinical, isolating, and completely ignored the fact that cooking together is supposed to be a bonding experience, not a math equation.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's why we built <strong class="text-v2-on-surface font-semibold">Couples Food System</strong>. We believe that sharing a meal is a cornerstone of a healthy relationship. Our mission is to remove the mental load of meal planning and the friction of dietary differences, so you can get back to what matters: enjoying dinner together.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong class="text-v2-on-surface font-semibold">V2 is our evolution.</strong> We built V1 for couples like us — partners with different dietary goals. Then we realized we were leaving out every couple who just wanted dinner without the stress. V2 adds a second way to cook: browse, pick, and shop for what you're craving, or let the pantry decide. Whether you're dieting or not, V2 works for you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Evolution to V2 -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-v2-on-surface">The Evolution to V2</h2>
      <div class="bg-v2-surface-container rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-v2-outline-variant">
        <p class="text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mb-6">
          V1 proved that couples want a shared food system. But it had one critical weakness: <strong class="text-v2-on-surface">no choice in meal selection.</strong> The AI generated one meal and that was it. No recipe database. No filtering by cuisine or cook time. No visual browsing. And it assumed both partners were dieting.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
          V2 fixes all of this. Two modes — Cook Now (pantry-first, zero shopping) and I Want This (browse, pick, shop) — give couples full agency over their dinner decisions. The adaptive cooking layer underneath remains the same: one meal, two plates, both perfect.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem We Saw -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-v2-on-surface">The Problem We Saw</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-v2-surface-container-lowest rounded-3xl border border-v2-outline-variant p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-v2-on-surface mb-2">The Mental Load</h3>
          <p class="text-v2-on-surface-variant">One person carries the entire burden of meal planning, grocery lists, and dinner decisions. It's invisible work that creates resentment over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-v2-surface-container-lowest rounded-3xl border border-v2-outline-variant p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-v2-on-surface mb-2">The Dietary Divide</h3>
          <p class="text-v2-on-surface-variant">When partners have different goals, they cook separately. Two meals, two grocery lists, twice the dishes. The shared kitchen becomes two solo kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-v2-surface-container-lowest rounded-3xl border border-v2-outline-variant p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-v2-on-surface mb-2">The Decision Fatigue</h3>
          <p class="text-v2-on-surface-variant">"What's for dinner?" is the question that starts the stress cycle every evening. 20 minutes of scrolling, still no answer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-v2-surface-container-lowest rounded-3xl border border-v2-outline-variant p-6 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-v2-on-surface mb-2">The Waste</h3>
          <p class="text-v2-on-surface-variant">$600/year lost to duplicate purchases and forgotten ingredients. Not just money — it's the frustration of watching food go bad.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Our Solution -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-v2-on-surface">Our Solution</h2>
      <div class="bg-v2-primary/10 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-v2-outline-variant">
        <p class="text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Couples Food System V2 is the flexible kitchen companion for every couple. Two ways to find dinner — cook from your pantry or browse what you're craving — one shared cooking experience underneath.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
          The result: one cooking session, two perfectly portioned plates, zero arguments. Whether you're dieting or not, V2 works for you. The food is just the medium — what we're really selling is less stress, fewer decisions, smoother evenings, and shared responsibility.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why Couples Food System -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8 text-center text-v2-on-surface">Why Couples Food System?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-v2-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We're not building another meal planning app. We're creating a new category: <strong class="text-v2-on-surface">Collaborative Adaptive Nutrition</strong>. No competitor combines real-time collaboration, adaptive portions, pantry-first AI, and relationship-first design into one system. The center of the market is empty — and we're filling it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <WaitlistV2>
    <WaitlistFormV2 />
  </WaitlistV2>
</BaseLayout>
